	<div class="posts">
	<a name="107386588562020546">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://csli-publications.stanford.edu/papers/mooneyabstract.html">Abstract for CSLI-97-202</a>.&nbsp; This is for "Searle's Chinese Room and its Aftermath" by Vincent John Mooney III.&nbsp; What caught my interest (while looking for something else) is the question whether "syntax causes semantics."&nbsp; I would think not, but I have no technical basis for that.&nbsp; Here's something to look int, if I can find the actual paper.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#107386588562020546">Sunday, January 11, 2004</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
